          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Your CIBC Smart Start questions answered\nCIBC Smart Start is great for everyday spending if you\u2019re under age 25. You\u2019ll receive unlimited everyday banking transactions \u24d8 including free Interac e-Transfer service \u24d8 for no monthly fee.\nNo, you can keep your existing account. You'll automatically receive all the benefits of CIBC\u00a0Smart Start, including unlimited everyday banking until you turn 25.\nWhen you turn 25, your CIBC Smart Start benefits will end and your account will continue as a regular CIBC Smart Account unless you're eligible for CIBC Smart for Students at that time.\nYour debit card number, account number and your online banking and mobile banking details will all remain the same.\nYes, the CIBC Smart Start benefits are available to any Canadian resident under age 25.\nYes, you're eligible to sign up if you're studying or living in Canada and you're under age 25.\nCIBC Smart Start",
